sible answers:\n\n- **No propagation:** keep turn-level evidence only, and compute session-level\n  summaries on read.\n- **Derived propagation:** expose session-level association as a derived query\n  from turn evidence.\n- **Persisted propagation:** write a session-level relationship when enough turn\n  evidence or user confirmation exists.\n\nThe cautious default is derived propagation plus sessio\n[TRUNCATED]\nld commit UI, PR/review publishing, or both ask the user\n  to confirm suggested sessions or turns?\n- Relationship scope: what is the smallest metadata shape that supports a\n  target-to-session relationship plus optional turn scope?\n- Propagation: if turn evidence points at a change id, should branch and PR\n  views derive that relationship, or should confirmed metadata be copied upward?\n- Plain Git operations: how should commits, rebases, and squashes outside\n  GitButler affect turn-derived evidence?\n\n## Implementation Implications\n\nThe current implementation in `crates/but-agentlog` already has the pieces that\nmake a turn layer plausible:\n\n- `record_transcript` snapshots a transcript file\n- `TranscriptBatch::parse` returns parsed records plus session/source metadata\n- `write_transcript_batch` filters records through `:record-hashes`\n- transcript records already carry `source_key`, `record_index`, and\n  `record_hash`\n\nThe missing piece is that `write_transcript_batch` throws away the batch\nboundary after appending records. A turn writer would need to receive the set of\nnewly accepted records and write a corresponding turn object.\n\nOne possible storage shape:\n\n```text\ngitbutler:agent-session:<session-key>:turns = list<TurnSummary JSON>\ngitbutler:agent-session:<session-key>:turn:<turn-key> = TurnDetail JSON\n```\n\nWhere `TurnSummary` is cheap to scan and `TurnDetail` contains record\nmembership plus the environment snapshot. The exact GitMeta representation needs\nchecking against list/set/record ergonomics.\n\n## Simplification Opportunity\n\nThis may also simplify deduplication conceptually:\n\n- record hashes answer \"have we stored this transcript record before?\"\n- turn membership answers \"which records were new in this capture invocation?\"\n- association evidence reads from turns instead of trying to infer everything\n  from a flat session transcript\n\nThat keeps the core POC principle intact: capture project-scoped session data\nfirst, then attach meaning through explicit relationships or carefully ranked\nsuggestions.\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T00:57:35.867Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}